\newlabel{tab:competitors}{{4}{7}{Head-to-head comparison. YaRN and PI are designed for post-hoc inference-time extension, not from-scratch training, and fail catastrophically in this regime}{table.4}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Passkey-retrieval mix (350M, base=500K, seed=42). Both methods achieve 100\% at 2K (in-distribution), proving both learned retrieval. The extrapolation gap is pure EVQ benefit: +40pp at 4K, +14pp at 8K. PPL waterbed is preserved (+0.8\% at 2K, $-4.4\%$ at 16K).}}{7}{table.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:passkey_mix}{{5}{7}{Passkey-retrieval mix (350M, base=500K, seed=42). Both methods achieve 100\% at 2K (in-distribution), proving both learned retrieval. The extrapolation gap is pure EVQ benefit: +40pp at 4K, +14pp at 8K. PPL waterbed is preserved (+0.8\% at 2K, $-4.4\%$ at 16K)}{table.5}{}}
